From: gmonsoon <greataji13@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 23:45:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] power: supply: qcom_fg: report charging status reliably

The qcom_fg battery never reflected charging on the Retroid Pocket 5:
pm8150b-charger reported online=1 status=Charging, but the battery
power supply (the one UPower/phosh shows) reported "Discharging", so no
charging indicator appeared.

Two bugs:

  1. The charger supply was looked up with
     power_supply_get_by_name("power-supplies") -- i.e. a supply whose
     *name* is literally "power-supplies". No such supply exists; the
     intent was the "power-supplies" DT phandle (the node already has
     power-supplies = <&pm8150b_charger>). The call always returned NULL,
     leaving chg_psy NULL, so the battery permanently used current-sign
     detection, which reports the wrong polarity here.

  2. Even once resolved, chip->status is only refreshed by the charger's
     power_supply_changed notifier and starts UNKNOWN, so a device booted
     already plugged in would still fall back to the broken path.

Resolve the charger from the DT phandle with power_supply_get_by_reference()
and propagate -EPROBE_DEFER so the fuel gauge binds reliably regardless of
probe order, and read the charger's status live in the STATUS handler
instead of trusting the event-driven cache. The charger remains
authoritative; current-based detection is only a last resort.

--- a/drivers/power/supply/qcom_fg.c
+++ b/drivers/power/supply/qcom_fg.c
@@ -886,12 +886,24 @@

 	switch (psp) {
 	case POWER_SUPPLY_PROP_STATUS:
-		/* Get status from charger if available */
-		if (chip->chg_psy &&
-			chip->status != POWER_SUPPLY_STATUS_UNKNOWN) {
-			val->intval = chip->status;
-			break;
-		} else {
+		/*
+		 * Prefer the charger's status, read live. The cached
+		 * chip->status is only refreshed on charger notifications and
+		 * starts UNKNOWN, so a device booted already plugged in would
+		 * otherwise fall through to current-based detection and never
+		 * report charging.
+		 */
+		if (chip->chg_psy) {
+			union power_supply_propval pval;
+
+			if (!power_supply_get_property(chip->chg_psy,
+					POWER_SUPPLY_PROP_STATUS, &pval) &&
+			    pval.intval != POWER_SUPPLY_STATUS_UNKNOWN) {
+				val->intval = pval.intval;
+				break;
+			}
+		}
+		{
 			/*
 			 * Fall back to capacity and current-based
 			 * status checking
@@ -1309,10 +1321,18 @@
 		return ret;
 	}

-	/* Optional: Get charger power supply for status checking */
-	chip->chg_psy = power_supply_get_by_name("power-supplies");
+	/*
+	 * Get the charger power supply for status checking. Resolve it from
+	 * the "power-supplies" DT phandle: power_supply_get_by_name() looked
+	 * up a supply literally named "power-supplies", which never exists, so
+	 * chg_psy was always NULL and the battery reported the wrong status.
+	 */
+	chip->chg_psy = power_supply_get_by_reference(dev_fwnode(chip->dev),
+						     "power-supplies");
 	if (IS_ERR(chip->chg_psy)) {
 		ret = PTR_ERR(chip->chg_psy);
+		if (ret == -EPROBE_DEFER)
+			return ret;
 		dev_warn(chip->dev, "Failed to get charger supply: %d\n", ret);
 		chip->chg_psy = NULL;
 	}
